Here is a basic example of a "Hello, World!" console application written in C#:

```csharp
// import the necessary library
using System;

// declare the namespace
namespace HelloWorldApp {
  
    // main class
    class Program {
      
        // main method
        static void Main(string[] args) {
          
          // prints hello world to the console
          Console.WriteLine("Hello, World!");

          // Stop the console from closing immediately
          Console.ReadKey();
        }
    }
}
```

This program will print out "Hello, World!" on the console. The `Console.ReadKey();` at the end is used to prevent the console window from closing immediately. This line waits for the user to press a key before the program ends.